<article id="post-3029" class="post-3029 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-general category-renovations">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2012/04/home-half-assembled-home/" rel="bookmark">Home, half-assembled home</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Well, our time out of the house has finally come to pass, and we&#8217;re back under a mostly-familiar roof. The roof itself is intact, and save for a taped-over vent hole (no longer in use) &#8212; it&#8217;s the inside that&#8217;s still in disarray.<br />
The renos are still on-going, and while we might be quite a ways further a long than when we moved out three week ago, we&#8217;re still a ways from having our house complete, functional, and dust-free.<br />
But at least it&#8217;s our house.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2012/04/home-half-assembled-home/#more-3029" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;Home, half-assembled home&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
