<article id="post-3011" class="post-3011 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-general category-renovations tag-bathroom tag-flooring tag-kitchen">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2012/03/the-kitchen-reno-moves-along/" rel="bookmark">The kitchen reno moves along</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<a class="post-thumbnail" href="http://geoff.wp/2012/03/the-kitchen-reno-moves-along/" aria-hidden="true">
			</a>

		
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Well, since I last wrote, much has happened in the house. In our previous installment, the floors were starting to come up. Since then, a lot as happened, and we&#8217;ve had the prerequisite miscommunications, strange discoveries, and mild panic attacks (from us, the client &#8212; our contractor is likely annoyed as hell with us at this point).<br />
But if there&#8217;s one thing I can say, we have progress. Lots of it.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2012/03/the-kitchen-reno-moves-along/#more-3011" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;The kitchen reno moves along&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
